</CENTER><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95%><TR><TD><B><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</FONT></A></B><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Class Balance & Class Bugs</FONT></A></B><BR><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Interrupt Nerf when running/stopping/casting ?</FONT></B></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><IMG SRC=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/new_topic.gif border=0></A>&nbsp; &nbsp; <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessage?topicID=251.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessage?topicID=234.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><TR><TD valign=top BACKGROUND= http://www.graffe.com/home/bar_back.gif><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top BACKGROUND= http://www.graffe.com/home/bar_back.gif><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearedanymore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfeared anymore</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/1/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3:00:00 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Interrupt Nerf when running/stopping/casting ?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I posted this on another Nerf post, but am curious..have any of you noticed it takes a 1/2 second longer to cast now, when attempting to cast after moving ?  It used to be, that if you ran, stopped, waited for the arms to come up to a 90 degree angle again(in f9 view), you could cast without interrupts..Now if you don't wait 1/2 sec AFTER the arms are up..you'll be interupted.  Seems like an obvious attempt to NERF kiting, and I believe this is accurate as I had been very used to the rythm of movement casting while Kiting and PvPing on my server for many levels.  Anyone else notice this ??  If it is so, the last patch was a beaut for wizards..*sigh*</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukindom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kindom</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/1/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>8:33:17 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Interrupt Nerf when running/stopping/casting ?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">its lagggg</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwankywiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WankyWiz</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/1/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>9:21:45 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Interrupt Nerf when running/stopping/casting ?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial"><br>
Try turning a small amount to either side right after you stop. This helps me, especially when I'm lagging a bit.<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucaldaer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caldaer</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/2/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>8:03:32 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">agreed</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Always when i'm running -- stopping -- casting..  i turn left or right just a touch and then cast..<br>
It takes longer for the game to realize you have stopped moving if you don't turn.. but if you turn left or right right after you have stopped moving forward/backward, then the game realizes almost in an instant that you are indeed not moving forward/backward.<br>
Takes a little bit to get used to, but i do it without thinking now, and have never had an interupt from stopping after running.<br>
<br>
-Caldaer <br>
51 Wiz</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/2/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>11:40:13 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Verants Answer...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">We have been given a work around for the &quot;on the fly interrupts&quot; awhile back.  However, it has been so long since we actully looked at the issue that it would be good to re-address.<br>
<br>
<br>
When I got a direct response from Verant in March of 2000, they gave this information...<br>
<br>
&quot;The aspect of motion in the game is controlled similarly to a simple on/off switch.  When you are in motion, the switch is turned on.  However, when you stop, it takes a period of about two seconds for the switch to turn off.  And a spell will be interrupted if the system still thinks you're moving.  The only way to FORCE the switch off when you stop is to turn in place.  It automatically switches the variable off.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Therefore, when kiting, it is always best to alternate between a forward arrow and a turning arrow.  Don't even stop in between the move and the turn.  Run, then turn in place a half-circle, fire the spell, wait for the pink bar to empty, complete the turn, run again.  You don't even have to wait until the spell hits.  Once that pink bar is empty, on most occassions, you will be ok to run again.  The turning in place REALLY makes all the difference.  You should be able to cast the spell without interrupt under a half-second from stopping.<br>
<br>
CAUTION - One thing you DON'T want to do is to turn a FULL 360 in place.  If you do that, the system recognizes that you are back in the direction you were running in the first place and may not flip the movement switch off.<br>
<br>
Fight well!<br>
<br>
W.F.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=95%><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessage?topicID=251.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessage?topicID=234.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95% BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=4><IMG SRC=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=249.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/images/email.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Email This To a Friend"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;Email This To a Friend</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=249.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Topic Control Image"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;Topic Commands (Moderator only)</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=249.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Subscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to receive email notification of replies</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=249.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Unsubscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</FONT><BR></TD><TD></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=3 ALIGN=CENTER><BR><FORM ACTION=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum METHOD=POST><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Jump to: </FONT><SELECT NAME=forumName><OPTION VALUE=graffeswizardcompilationfrm1>Gener